But I cannot discern her. She remains as nebulous as my best poem—the one you made such gruesome fun of in the Literaturnïe Zapiski. When I want to imagine her, I have to cling mentally to a tiny brown birthmark on her downy forearm, as one concentrates upon a punctuation mark in an illegible sentence. Perhaps, had she used a greater amount of make-up or used it more constantly, I might have visualized her fa